'''''Coriaria thymifolia''''', known as '''shanshi''', is a plant found in the northern [[Andes]]. The plant is often mistaken for blueberries,{{citation needed|date=January 2016}} however unlike blueberries, the fruit of the Shanshi is toxic and has hallucinogenic properties.<ref name="Golden Guide to Hallucinogenics">{{cite web|title=The Vaults of Erowid|url=http://www.erowid.org/library/books_online/golden_guide/g101-110.shtml|accessdate=6 August 2013}}</ref>

